# ATTACH IAM ROLE TO EC2 INSTANCE (S3 ACCESS WITHOUT KEYS)
## OBJECTIVE
Provide secure access to Amazon S3 from an EC2 instance using an IAM Role (no access keys required).
---
## STEP 1: CREATE IAM ROLE
1. Open AWS Management Console  
2. Go to IAM  
3. Click Roles  
4. Click Create role  
5. Select Trusted entity: AWS Service  
6. Use case: EC2  
7. Click Next  
---
## STEP 2: ADD PERMISSIONS
1. Search for policy: AmazonS3FullAccess  
2. Select the policy  
3. Click Next  
---
## STEP 3: NAME THE ROLE
1. Role name: EC2-S3-Role  
2. Click Create role  
---
## STEP 4: ATTACH ROLE TO EC2 INSTANCE
1. Go to EC2 Dashboard  
2. Select your running instance  
3. Click Actions  
4. Navigate: Security → Modify IAM role  
5. Select role: EC2-S3-Role  
6. Click Update  
---
## STEP 5: VERIFY FROM EC2 INSTANCE (NO ACCESS KEYS)
### Connect to EC2 Instance
1. Open terminal / SSH into instance  
### Run Commands
sudo apt update
sudo apt install awscli
---
#### List S3 Buckets
aws s3 ls
aws ec2 describe-instances
#### Create a new S3 Bucket
aws s3 mb s3://your-unique-bucket-name
---

## EXPECTED RESULT
- EC2 instance can access S3 without access keys  
- Temporary credentials are automatically provided by IAM role  
- Secure and recommended method for AWS access  

---

## CONCLUSION
- IAM Roles eliminate need for storing access keys  
- Provides secure, temporary access to AWS services  
- Best practice for EC2 to S3 communication  
